In [46]:
def do_tsne(frame, name, year=2012,perplexity=35):
    import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
    import seaborn as sns
    %matplotlib inline
    from sklearn.manifold import TSNE
    data = frame[['index_1', 'index_2', 'index_3', 'index_4', 'index_5']][(frame['academic_year'] == year) & (frame['sector'] != 0)]
    tsne = TSNE(perplexity=perplexity)
    Y = tsne.fit_transform(data)
    new_frame = frame[(frame['academic_year'] == year) & (frame['sector'] != 0)].copy()
    new_frame['tsne1'] = Y[:,0]
    new_frame['tsne2'] = Y[:,1]
    sns.lmplot(x='tsne1', y='tsne2', hue='sector', col='sector', fit_reg=False, data=new_frame, col_wrap =3)
    plt.savefig(name + '.pdf')
    return new_frame
